DESCRIPTION:Kiwanis Club of Roanoke partners with Melrose Library\, Goodwi
 ll Industries\, Shiloh Baptist Church and the Melrose Hub as well as publ
 ic groups like the Police Dept and Sheriff\, plus another 50 nonprofits w
 ho offer activities for children and their families including entertainme
 nt (music and dancing).  Shiloh Baptist Church will grill and serve hambu
 rgers and hot dogs for attendees.  The event is open to the public from 1
 1 to 3 pm and is advertised widely encouraging community participation. T
 he goal is promoting healthy activity and community strengthening so the 
 Kiwanis Centennial Playground is a focal point.  This space is reserved b
 ut open to all for play and exercise. No charge to participate by any org
 anization or individuals.   https://www.roanokeva.gov/calendar.aspx?EID=8
 864
