BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:The Local Colors Festival celebrates the global diversity in t
 he region by bringing many different cultures together for a day of festi
 vities. The event opens with a Procession of Nations at 11:00 am. After t
 hat\, performances of dance\, music\, and martial arts demonstrations rep
 resenting many different cultures run from 12:00 - 5:00 pm at the Amphith
 eater. Vendor booths of various cuisine\, artisan crafts\, cultural displ
 ays and community services fill the park and Franklin Avenue. A children'
 s area offers young festival goers the opportunity to learn about differe
 nt cultures with fun\, interactive activities plus a Passport Program. Ad
 ditionally there is an international beer garden for adults. This family-
 friendly event offers a global experience right in one place and admissio
 n is free.  https://www.roanokeva.gov/calendar.aspx?EID=8608
