BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:What if there was a race where you could compete with speed OR
  strength? That’s what weighted racing is all about! The inaugural Roanok
 e Valley Weighted Race will take place Saturday Aprill 11\, 2026.  \nYou 
 choose how much weight to carry at the start of each lap of the 2.5 mile 
 out-and-back course\, from River’s Edge North to Piedmont Park and back. 
 That weight will be multiplied by the lap distance to arrive at your scor
 e\, in pound-miles – which we call “Kz.” Carry 10 pounds and score 25 Kz 
 for that lap. Add\, subtract or keep the same weight for the next lap. Do
  as many laps as you like\, but you’ll need to finish your last lap befor
 e time expires. Be as creative as you like with what – and how – you carr
 y it: ruck / backpack\, weighted vest\, sandbag…hydration bladder with so
 me weight in it. As long as you can carry it\, we’ll weigh it.  https://w
 ww.roanokeva.gov/calendar.aspx?EID=8537
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T140000
DTSTAMP;TZID=America/New_York:20260128T074424
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260411T080000
LAST-MODIFIED;TZID=America/New_York:20260128T074424
LOCATION:<p>River&apos\;s Edge Sports Complex - North</p> -   Roanoke VA 2
 4011
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Weighted Racing is Coming to Roanoke!
